dat_arousal_long = dat %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = c(dplyr::ends_with("_dif")),
               names_to = "emot_type",
               values_to = "emot_value") %>% 
  dplyr::filter(emot_type %in% c("excitation_dif", "valence_dif"))


new_labels <- c("excitation_dif" = "Change in arousal (post- minus pre-test)", 
                "valence_dif" = "Change in valence (post- minus pre-test)")

dat_emot_long = dat %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = c(dplyr::ends_with("_dif")),
               names_to = "emot_type",
               values_to = "emot_value")

dat_emot_long$model_emot = ifelse(dat_emot_long$emot_type %in% c("valence_dif", "excitation_dif"), "dimensional", "discrete")


new_labels <- c("joy_dif" = "Change in Joy (post- minus pre-test)", 
                "anger_dif" = "Change in Anger (post- minus pre-test)", 
                "disgust_dif" = "Change in Disgust (post- minus pre-test)", 
                "amusement_dif" = "Change in Amusement (post- minus pre-test)", 
                "sadness_dif" = "Change in Sadness (post- minus pre-test)", 
                "fear_dif" = "Change in Fear (post- minus pre-test)")

dat_emot_long$emot_typeF <- factor(dat_emot_long$emot_type, 
                                     levels = c("joy_dif", "amusement_dif", "sadness_dif", 
                                                "anger_dif", "disgust_dif", "fear_dif"))

Post-hoc + adjusted SMD

post_hoc_films = emmeans(mlm_films, 
                         trt.vs.ctrlk ~ Valence | list_emots, 
                         mult.name = "list_emots", adjust = "none")

res_films = data.frame(test(post_hoc_films, 
                        adjust = "none")$contrasts)
res_films$p.value = res_films$p.value * 12
dat_sd = dat %>% 
         group_by(Valence) %>%
         summarise(
             n = n(),
             sd_joy = sd(joy_post),
             sd_amusemennt = sd(amusement_post),
             sd_fear = sd(fear_post),
             sd_sadness = sd(sadness_post),
             sd_disgust = sd(disgust_post),
             sd_anger = sd(anger_post))
dat_em = data.frame(post_hoc_films$emmeans)
dat_smd_raw = dplyr::left_join(dat_em, dat_sd)
## Joining, by = "Valence"
dat_joy_sad = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence != "Neutral")
dat_neut = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence == "Neutral")
colnames(dat_neut) = paste0(colnames(dat_neut), "_neut")
dat_neut$list_emots = dat_neut$list_emots_neut
dat_smd = dplyr::left_join(dat_joy_sad, dat_neut)
## Joining, by = "list_emots"
dat_smd$sd_1 = with(dat_smd,
  ifelse(list_emots=="fear_post", sd_fear,
         ifelse(list_emots=="anger_post", sd_anger,
                ifelse(list_emots=="disgust_post", sd_disgust,
                       ifelse(list_emots=="amusement_post", sd_amusemennt,
                              ifelse(list_emots=="joy_post", sd_joy,
                                     ifelse(list_emots=="sadness_post", sd_sadness, NA)))))))
dat_smd$sd_2 = with(dat_smd,
  ifelse(list_emots=="fear_post", sd_fear_neut,
         ifelse(list_emots=="anger_post", sd_anger_neut,
                ifelse(list_emots=="disgust_post", sd_disgust_neut,
                       ifelse(list_emots=="amusement_post", sd_amusemennt_neut,
                              ifelse(list_emots=="joy_post", sd_joy_neut,
                                     ifelse(list_emots=="sadness_post", sd_sadness_neut, NA)))))))

       
es = compute.es::mes(m.1=dat_smd$emmean, m.2=dat_smd$emmean_neut, 
         sd.1=dat_smd$sd_1, sd.2=dat_smd$sd_2, 
         n.1=dat_smd$n, n.2=dat_smd$n_neut, verbose = FALSE)
res_films$smd = es$d
res_films$smd_lo = es$l.d
res_films$smd_up = es$u.d

post_hoc_films = emmeans(mlm_films, 
                         trt.vs.ctrlk ~ Valence | list_emots, 
                         mult.name = "list_emots", adjust = "none")
res_films = data.frame(test(post_hoc_films, 
                       adjust = "none")$contrasts)
dat_sd = dat %>% 
         group_by(Valence) %>%
         summarise(
             n = n(),
             sd_valence = sd(valence_post),
             sd_excitation= sd(excitation_post))

dat_smd_raw = dplyr::left_join(dat_em, dat_sd)
## Joining, by = "Valence"

dat_neut = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence == "Neutral")

dat_neut$list_emots = dat_neut$list_emots_neut
dat_smd = dplyr::left_join(dat_joy_sad, dat_neut)
## Joining, by = "list_emots"
dat_smd$sd_1 = ifelse(dat_smd$list_emots=="valence_post", 
                      dat_smd$sd_valence, 
                      dat_smd$sd_excitation)
dat_smd$sd_2 = ifelse(dat_smd$list_emots=="valence_post", 
                      dat_smd$sd_valence_neut,

         n.1=dat_smd$n, n.2=dat_smd$n_neut, verbose = FALSE)

Logistic regression

Model

glm_framing = glm(risky_choice ~ Framing * Valence + joy_pre + sadness_pre,
                  data = dat,
                  family = "binomial",
                  contrasts=list(
                    Framing=contr.sum, 
                    Valence=contr.sum))

car::Anova(glm_framing, type = "III")

S4. Supplementary analyses (reviewers)

dat_cluster = dat %>%
  select((ends_with("_pre") | ends_with("_post")) & !starts_with("valence") & !starts_with("excitatio")) %>%
  scale()


clust = kmeans(dat_cluster, 3, nstart = 25)

dat$cluster = as.character(clust$cluster)
factoextra ::fviz_cluster(clust, data = dat_cluster,
             palette = c("#2E9FDF", "#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "red"), 
             geom = "point",
             ellipse.type = "convex", 
             ggtheme = theme_bw()
             )

glm_framing = glm(risky_choice ~ Framing * cluster,
                  data = dat,
                  family = "binomial",
                  contrasts=list(
                    Framing=contr.sum, 
                    cluster=contr.sum))
